Signature (rewritingsystem):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a rewriting system then truth holds)

Signature (term):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a term then v0 is an object)

Signature (reduct):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v1 is a term then for all v2, (if v2 is a reduct of v1 in v0 then v2 is a term)))

Signature:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v1 is a term and v2 is a term then (if v1 - v0 +> v2 then truth holds))))

Axiom (tcdef):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v1 is a term and v2 is a term then (v1 - v0 +> v2 iff (v2 is a reduct of v1 in v0 or for some v3, (v3 is a term and v3 is a reduct of v1 in v0 and v3 - v0 +> v2))))))

Axiom (tctrans):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (for all v3, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v1 is a term and v2 is a term and v3 is a term then (if v1 - v0 +> v2 and v2 - v0 +> v3 then v1 - v0 +> v3)))))

Definition (tcrdef):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v1 is a term and v2 is a term then ((v1 - v0 *> v2) iff (v1 is equal to v2 or v1 - v0 +> v2)))))

Theorem (tcrtrans):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (for all v3, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v1 is a term and v2 is a term and v3 is a term then (if v1 - v0 *> v2 and v2 - v0 *> v3 then v1 - v0 *> v3)))))
Proof:
Qed.

Definition (crdef):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a rewriting system then ((v0 is confluent) iff for all v1, (for all v2, (for all v3, (if v1 is a term and v2 is a term and v3 is a term and (v1 - v0 *> v2 and v1 - v0 *> v3) then for some v4, (v4 is a term and v2 - v0 *> v4 and v3 - v0 *> v4))))))

Definition (wcrdef):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a rewriting system then ((v0 is locally confluent) iff for all v1, (for all v2, (for all v3, (if v1 is a term and v2 is a term and v3 is a term and (v2 is a reduct of v1 in v0 and v3 is a reduct of v1 in v0) then for some v4, (v4 is a term and v2 - v0 *> v4 and v3 - v0 *> v4))))))

Definition (termin):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a rewriting system then ((v0 is terminating) iff for all v1, (for all v2, (if v1 is a term and v2 is a term then (if v1 - v0 +> v2 then v2 is inductively less than v1)))))

Definition (nfrdef):
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v1 is a term then for all v2, ((v2 is a normal form of v1 in v0) iff (v2 is a term and v1 - v0 *> v2 and it is wrong that (for some v3, (v3 is a reduct of v2 in v0))))))

Theorem (termnf):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v0 is terminating then for all v1, (if v1 is a term then (if for all v2, (if v2 is a term then (if v2 is inductively less than v1 then for some v3, (v3 is a normal form of v2 in v0))) then for some v2, (v2 is a normal form of v1 in v0))))
Proof:
Qed.

Theorem (newman):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a rewriting system and v0 is terminating and v0 is locally confluent then v0 is confluent)
Proof:
  R is a rewriting system
  R is locally confluent and R is terminating
  for all v0, (for all v1, (for all v2, (if v0 is a term and v1 is a term and v2 is a term and (v0 - R *> v1 and v0 - R *> v2) then (if for all v3, (for all v4, (for all v5, (if v3 is a term and v4 is a term and v5 is a term and (v3 - R *> v4 and v3 - R *> v5) then (if v3 is inductively less than v0 then for some v6, (v6 is a term and v4 - R *> v6 and v5 - R *> v6))))) then for some v3, (v3 is a term and v1 - R *> v3 and v2 - R *> v3)))))
  Proof:
    a is a term and b is a term and c is a term
    if a - R +> b and a - R +> c then the thesis holds
    Proof:
      a - R +> b and a - R +> c
      u is a term and u is a reduct of a in R and u - R *> b
      v is a term and v is a reduct of a in R and v - R *> c
      w is a term and u - R *> w and v - R *> w
      d is a normal form of w in R
      b - R *> d
      Proof:
        x is a term and b - R *> x and d - R *> x
      Qed.
      c - R *> d
      Proof:
        y is a term and c - R *> y and d - R *> y
      Qed.
    Qed.
  Qed.
Qed.

